  m_Name: Lumbar_Vertebrae_L4_L6
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Lumbar_Vertebrae_L4_L6
  partName: Lumbar Vertebrae L4 L6
  descriptionChunks:
  - The lumbar vertebrae L4 through L6 form the middle to caudal section of the canine
    lumbar spine and support significant mechanical loads during movement. These
    vertebrae provide flexibility for bending and extension while maintaining stability
    of the lower back. Their robust structure serves as an attachment site
  - for major muscles controlling trunk motion and hindlimb propulsion. The lumbar
    vertebrae also protect spinal nerves responsible for sensory and motor function
    within the pelvic limbs. Efficient locomotion depends on healthy alignment and
    coordinated muscular support within this region.
